Working Area
 
Staging Area
 
Commited Area
 
 
git config user.name <username>
git config user.email <email>
 
git init   => initialzie git 
git add  <filename/s>  => add files to the Staging
git commit -m <commit message>
git status  => to see status for current working/staging Area
git log     => to see the logs of the commits already doesn
.gitignore  => add file names you don't want git to track here 
git --help => to list git availabe commands
git help <specific command> | git <command> --help


git log --name-only => list the names of files updated
git log --oneline   => see logs with a commit in each entry
git log -n <numberofcommits> => to see a specfic number of commits

git branch <branchname> => to create a new branch
git checkout -b <branchname> => to create a new branch and switch to it
git switch || git checkout   => to switch to a different branch
git log <branchname> to see the log of a branch

# To authenticate to github using ssh
ssh-keygen  => keep pressing enter
cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub
copy the content 
go to github, => setting, SSH and GPG keys => add new key 
in the key section, paste and add any title 
press Add SSH key

git merge <branchname> => to merge to current branch
git remote add <alias> <repo url>  => alias is just a name for your remote repo 
git push <remoterepo> <branch>
git push -u  <remoterepo> <branch> => local repo will always follow that remote repo
git push 
